In its continuous bid to reposition Nigeria for economic growth, the Federal Government is in talks with the China Development Bank  (CDB) to invest in key sectors of the economy. The Vice Chairman and President of the China Development Bank, Zheng Zhigie who disclosed this to journalists when he led his team to meet with the Finance Minister, Mrs Kemi Adeosun in Abuja pledged targeted investments in Agriculture, Infrastructure and the health sectors of the nation.  Our correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that he said this is in response to strengthening of Bilateral relationship between Nigeria and China following the visit of President Muhammadu Buhari to China in 2016. In her remarks, the Minister of Finance, Mrs Kemi Adeosun who commended the Bank for their interest in Nigeria said the focus would be to discuss in specifics how to seal some of the transactions to the benefit of the nations. 